OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778637819
OL,3,C'Alarmingly high' levels of salt found
OL,4,Cin some of UK's most popular sandwiches
OL,6,FSome of the UK's most popular shop-
OL,7,Fbought sandwiches contain "alarmingly
OL,8,Fhigh" levels of salt, with one
OL,9,Fcontaining more than the equivalent of
OL,10,Falmost five McDonald's cheeseburgers,
OL,11,Faccording to a study.
OL,13,FThe charity Action on Salt & Sugar
OL,14,Fanalysed 546 sandwiches, wraps, rolls
OL,15,Fand baguettes sold in supermarkets and
OL,16,Fhigh street chains to find that one in
OL,17,Ften exceeded the salt and calorie
OL,18,Fhealth targets.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778637819
OL,3,C'Alarmingly high' levels of salt found
OL,4,Cin some of UK's most popular sandwiches
OL,6,FAlmost half (44%) would carry a red or
OL,7,F"high" salt warning on their front-of-
OL,8,Fpack labelling, while 32 deliver half
OL,9,For more of an adult's maximum daily
OL,10,Flimit in a single serving, it found.
OL,12,FThe charity named the Smoked Chicken
OL,13,FCaesar Club, sold by upmarket cafe
OL,14,Fchain Gail's, as the "worst offender",
OL,15,Ffinding that it contained a
OL,16,F"staggering" 6.88g of salt, equivalent
OL,17,Fto nearly ten rashers of bacon or five
OL,18,FMcDonald's cheeseburgers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778637819
OL,3,C'Alarmingly high' levels of salt found
OL,4,Cin some of UK's most popular sandwiches
OL,6,FAdults should consume no more than 6g
OL,7,Fof salt a day ` or around one level
OL,8,Fteaspoon ` according to UK health
OL,9,Fguidelines.
OL,11,FFurthermore, the sandwich also
OL,12,Fcontains over 1000 calories and 90% of
OL,13,Fan adult's maximum daily saturated fat
OL,14,Flimit, while providing only 20% of an
OL,15,Fadult's recommended fibre intake, the
OL,16,Fstudy found.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1778637819
OL,3,C'Alarmingly high' levels of salt found
OL,4,Cin some of UK's most popular sandwiches
OL,6,FHowever, the wider picture was equally
OL,7,Fpoor, with researchers finding that a
OL,8,Fthird of sandwiches surveyed would
OL,9,Freceive a red warning on front-of-pack
OL,10,Flabelling for saturated fat, and more
OL,11,Fthan one in seven were high in fat,
OL,12,Fsaturated fat and salt simultaneously.
OL,14,FAlmost all the sandwiches surveyed
OL,15,F(97%) failed to provide even a third
OL,16,Fof the daily recommended fibre intake.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
